    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                    
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.4.23-24_0001" />
                
                <opener>
                                            <dateline>
                                                        May 
                                                     Twenty-eight
                                                        1917
                                            </dateline>
                  
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt,</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Bancroft, Nebraska.</addrLine>
                    </address>

                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt: &#8212;</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>At a recent meeting of the University Regents it was voted to recommend that the Regents confer upon you the honory degree of Doctor of Letters on Commencement Day, June 13.</p>
    
                <p>Speaking for the Regents, I am sure that they will be pleased to ratify this action of the University Senate if it will be agreeable to you to accept the degree and possible for you to be present to receive it.</p>
    
                <p>As the preparation of an appropriate diploma requires a little time, will you please acknowledge receipt of this letter at your earliest convenience.</p>
                <closer>
                                                            <salute>Yours very sincerely,</salute>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>


            <div1 type="enclosure">
                                                                                                                                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.4.23-24_0002"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">24</fw>
            
                <opener>
                                                    <dateline>May 29th, '17.</dateline>

                    <address>
                        <addrLine><hi rend="caps">S.</hi> Avery, Chancellor,</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Lincoln, Nebraska.</addrLine>
                    </address>

                    <salute>Dear Mr. Avery:&#8212;</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Your letter of the 28th makes me very happy, and I hasten to express my deep appreciation of the honor that the University of my home state proposes to confer upon me.</p>
    
                <p>I accept the offer, and will arrange to be present on June 13th to receive the degree.</p>
                <closer>
                                                    <salute>Sincerely,</salute>

                                                    <signed>Jno. G. Neihardt</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
